SIMPLE: chalkstone
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chalkstone
<hw>Chalk"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
mass of chalk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As <qex>chalkstones</qex> . . . beaten in sunder.</q>
<rj><qau>Isa. xxvii. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A chalklike concretion, consisting
mainly of urate of sodium, found in and about the small joints, in the
external ear, and in other situations, in those affected with gout; a
tophus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chalky</ent>⟦br⟧
